Body Schema

Type: object

A planet or body to generate

root name
Type: string
Default: "New planet"

Unique name of your planet

root starSystem
Type: string
Default: "SolarSystem"

Unique star system containing your planet

root destroy
Type: boolean
Default: false

True if you want to delete this planet

root base
Type: object

root base hasMapMarker
Type: boolean
Default: false

root base hasAmbientLight
Type: boolean
Default: false

root base surfaceGravity
Type: number
Default: 12

The acceleration due to gravity felt as the surfaceSize. Timber Hearth has 12 for reference

root base gravityFallOff
Type: enum (of string)
Default: "linear"

Must be one of:

  • "linear"
  • "inverseSquared"

root base surfaceSize
Type: number
Default: 100

A scale height used for a number of things.

root base sphereOfInfluence
Type: number
Default: 0

An override for the radius of the planet's gravitational sphere of influence. Optional

root base groundSize
Type: number
Default: 0

Radius of the a simple sphere used as the ground for the planet. If you want to use more complex terrain, leave this as 0.

root base hasCometTail
Type: boolean
Default: false

root base hasReferenceFrame
Type: boolean
Default: true

Allows the object to be targeted on the map.

root base centerOfSolarSystem
Type: boolean
Default: false

Set this to true if you are replacing the sun with a different body. Only one object in a star system should ever have this set to true.

root base isSatellite
Type: boolean
Default: false

Is this body an artificial satellite of a planet/moon/star?

Type: object

Type: number
Default: 0

root atmosphere cloudTint r

Default: 0

Value must be greater or equal to 0 and lesser or equal to 255

Relative filepath to the cloud texture, if the planet has clouds. Optional.

root atmosphere cloudCap
Type: string

Relative filepath to the cloud cap texture, if the planet has clouds. Optional.

root atmosphere cloudRamp
Type: string

Relative filepath to the cloud ramp texture, if the planet has clouds. Optional.

root atmosphere useBasicCloudShader
Type: boolean
Default: false

Use Giant's deep shader or just apply the cloud texture as is.

root atmosphere shadowsOnClouds
Type: boolean
Default: true

If the top layer should have shadows

root atmosphere fogTint
Type: object

Colour of fog on the planet.

root atmosphere fogTint r
Type: integer
Default: 0

Value must be greater or equal to 0 and lesser or equal to 255

root atmosphere fogTint g
Type: integer
Default: 0

Value must be greater or equal to 0 and lesser or equal to 255

root atmosphere fogTint b
Type: integer
Default: 0

root atmosphere fogTint a
Type: integer
Default: 0

Value must be greater or equal to 0 and lesser or equal to 255

root atmosphere fogDensity
Type: number

Value must be greater or equal to 0 and lesser or equal to 1

root atmosphere fogSize
Type: number

Radius of fog sphere, independent of the atmosphere

Value must be greater or equal to 0

root atmosphere hasRain
Type: boolean
Default: false

root atmosphere hasSnow
Type: boolean
Default: false

root atmosphere hasOxygen
Type: boolean
Default: false

Default: false

Type: integer

root orbit
Type: object

root orbit semiMajorAxis
Type: integer
Default: 5000

The average distance between the planet and its primary body.

Value must be greater or equal to 0

root orbit inclination
Type: number
Default: 0

The angle (in degrees) between the body's orbit and the plane of the star system

root orbit primaryBody
Type: string
Default: "Sun"

The name of the body this one will orbit around

root orbit isMoon
Type: boolean

Is this the moon of a planet?

root orbit longitudeOfAscendingNode
Type: number
Default: 0

root orbit eccentricity
Type: number
Default: 0

Value must be greater or equal to 0 and lesser or equal to 0.99

root orbit argumentOfPeriapsis
Type: number
Default: 0

root orbit trueAnomaly
Type: number
Default: 0

root orbit axialTilt
Type: number
Default: 0

root orbit siderealPeriod
Type: number
Default: 0

root orbit isTidallyLocked
Type: boolean
Default: false

root orbit showOrbitLine
Type: boolean
Default: false

root orbit isStatic
Type: boolean
Default: false

Is the body meant to stay in one place without moving?

root orbit tint
Type: object

Colour of the orbit-line in the map view.

root orbit tint r
Type: integer
Default: 0

Value must be greater or equal to 0 and lesser or equal to 255

root orbit tint g
Type: integer
Default: 0

Value must be greater or equal to 0 and lesser or equal to 255

root orbit tint b
Type: integer
Default: 0

Value must be greater or equal to 0 and lesser or equal to 255

root orbit tint a
Type: integer
Default: 0

Value must be greater or equal to 0 and lesser or equal to 255

root orbit trackingOrbitLine
Type: boolean
Default: false

Should we just draw a line behind its orbit.

root props reveal
Type: array of object

A set of volumes that reveal ship log fact

Each item of this array must be:

root props reveal reveal items
Type: object

root props reveal reveal items revealOn
Type: enum (of string)

'enter', 'observe', or 'snapshot' what needs to be done to the volume to unlock the facts

Must be one of:

  • "enter"
  • "observe"
  • "snapshot"

root props reveal reveal items reveals
Type: array of string

A list of facts to reveal

Each item of this array must be:

root props reveal reveal items reveals reveals items
Type: string

root props reveal reveal items position
Type: object

The position to place the volume at

root props reveal reveal items position x
Type: number
Default: 0

root props reveal reveal items position y
Type: number
Default: 0

root props reveal reveal items position z
Type: number
Default: 0

root props reveal reveal items radius
Type: number
Default: 1.0

The radius of the volume

root props reveal reveal items maxDistance
Type: number

The max distance the user can be away from the volume to reveal the fact (snapshot and observe only)

root props reveal reveal items maxAngle
Type: number
Default: 180.0

The max view angle (in degrees) the player can see the volume with to unlock the fact

Type: number
Default: 0

root signal signals signals items position y
Type: number
Default: 0

root signal signals signals items position z
Type: number
Default: 0

root signal signals signals items frequency
Type: enum (of string)

Must be one of:

  • "Default"
  • "Traveler"
  • "Quantum"
  • "EscapePod"
  • "Statue"
  • "WarpCore"
  • "HideAndSeek"
  • "Radio"

root signal signals signals items name
Type: string

root signal signals signals items audioClip
Type: string

Name of an existing AudioClip in the game

root signal signals signals items audioFilePath
Type: string

Relative filepath to the .wav file to use as the audio. Mutually exclusive with audioClip

root signal signals signals items reveals
Type: string

A ship log fact to reveal when the signal is identified

root signal signals signals items sourceRadius
Type: number
Default: 1

Radius of the sphere giving off the signal

root signal signals signals items detectionRadius
Type: number

How close the player must get to the signal to detect it

Value must be greater or equal to 0

root signal signals signals items identificationRadius
Type: number

How close the player must get to the signal to identify it

Value must be greater or equal to 0

root signal signals signals items onlyAudibleToScope
Type: boolean
Default: true

False if the player can hear the signal without equipping the signal-scope

root signal signals signals items insideCloak
Type: boolean
Default: false

Only set to true if you are putting this signal inside a cloaking field
